snippet.title: Prime Numbers as Building Blocks - Euclid's greatest discovery
snippet.description: Euclid identified Prime Numbers as building blocks for all numbers. This leads to the discovery of unique factorization. This idea lies at the heart of modern encryption techniques such as RSA.
